annotationA: Xeroderma pigmentosum D is a DNA helicase that is a subunit of the basal transcription and DNA repair factor TFIIH
annotationB: Transcription elongation factor S-II; Necessary for efficient RNA polymerase II transcription elongation past template-encoded arresting sites. The arresting sites in DNA have the property of trapping a certain fraction of elongating RNA polymerases that pass through, resulting in locked ternary complexes. Cleavage of the nascent transcript by S-II allows the resumption of elongation from the new 3'-terminus
